text:
Confirmed. Those are the correct coordinates.
See you up north.
All units have been apprised of the temple's location.

This keystone curse stuff?
It sounds like it might be the real deal.
Everyone who's ever used it has ended up dead.
To be precise, those who enter the temple are never seen again. "Vanished" doesn't mean "dead."
Either way, the president's sending us to our deaths.
Uh, I dunno. Maybe because it's a terrible idea? Although, that's kinda on-brand for him.
We'll arrive first and roll out the welcome mat.
Got 'em. They're headed for the northern continent.

Can I get there?
Only with one arm tied behind my back!

Girl might be missin' her wings,
but long as you got me, it'll be smooth sailin'.
Oh, man...this is gonna be rough.
What can I say? Life is full of ups and downs.
They've mobilized the Turks and the military.
Hope you're ready for a fight.

I hope you realize, this "temple" of yours
is not, in fact, the promised land.

The beginning of the end.
The celebration of the faithful.
A watershed moment for all mankind.
But the temple itself? Merely the stage.
Are you sure this is the place?
Alright, mateys. Time to hoist the sails!

Y'all ready?
Then batten down the hatches and hold on tight!

Land here?
You will not be able to return after landing.

Waves did a number on the ol' gal.
Gonna give 'er a once-over.
I'll catch up─just gotta tend to her first.
Can't wait to get some wings on my baby again...
Being outside is exhausting... I hate it.
What is man in the face of the natural world?
The Ancients built all this? Damn.
"We who are born of the planet, with her we speak. Her flesh we shape.
"Unto her promised land shall we one day return.

"By her loving grace and providence
may we take our place in paradise."
Oh... No. This isn't the promised land.
Not with all this sadness...and anger.
They didn't waste any time, the greedy sons of bitches.
What the hell's wrong with this place!?
This is one hell of a mess.

Yeah, but...they didn't have Aerith!
We get a free pass, right!?
I tried, but...no free pass for us.

Now, I know I came with y'all this far,
but I ain't about to go in there.

You've done so much for us already.
We'll always be grateful, Cid.
So when you're ready, I'll be here.
Find me when you're done. Bronco's ready when you are.
Sorry, but there ain't nothin' in the world that could make me go in there.
The Ancient has entered the temple.
This is going to be interesting.
Sephiroth's beat us to the punch.
C'mon. We don't have much time.

Look at it!
The Ancients built all this just to hide something?
That black materia's gotta be worth a fortune!

Not another word about the black materia.
We can't let Shinra find out.

Doesn't matter if they know or not.
We just need to find it first.

I could be wrong, but I'm starting to think
we checked our sanity at the door.
The only "promised" thing here is death for us all.
Sir. Avalanche and the Ancient─they're here.
I say we set an ambush and take 'em out!
No, we focus on the mission.
Our orders were to find proof that this is indeed the promised land─so we will split up and search.
Reno, Rude, pair off. Elena, you're with me.
See you keep your priorities straight.
This temple's daunting enough without Shinra and the black robes complicatin' things.
Got a real bad feelin' 'bout all this.
This place can sense our emotions─turn 'em against us.
The blood... I can almost smell it.
There was a great battle here long ago. So many lives lost...
Well, legend says no one who enters the temple ever comes out.
Why am I only hearing this now!?
Asshole was prob'ly lyin' through his teeth. Don't pay it no mind.
We just get turned upside down!?
Or the temple did. Depends how you look at it.
Uh, wasn't that waterfall going sideways just a second ago?
It was─at least I think it was. Wonder where it goes.
Wonder all you want, but I don't care to find out.
This is the only way we can catch up to the others! Now jump, goddammit!
Okay, just...give me a moment, sir!
No way to go but down.
I can't believe we're doin' this.
Don't look down don't look down don't look down!
We hold this position until the Turks send word. Check your gear and be ready to depart at a moment's notice.
Wouldn't be a labyrinth without a guardian, right?
At least, that's how it feels.
Hey, Aerith. Do you think you could explain that we don't mean any harm?
The materia's our priority. We have to get to it first.
They're with Aerith. They'll be fine.
Maybe we can block it with something nearby?
Goddamn... This place is a death trap!
We're lucky we managed to survive this long!
Don't jinx it! Just shut up and get to work.
We're goin' as fast as we can!
Still owe you both for Sector 7.
Could say the same for you.
It's a shame we'll have to settle up later.
Guess we'll just have to pick this up next time.
Don't beat yourself up. First time and all that.
Just gotta keep at it. Starting right now.
Yeah... Yeah, you're right. Can't give up now.
You don't think anything bad'll happen to them...do you?
So long as Cloud can keep it together.
Tifa's just gotta crack the whip a little.
Tell him to snap out of it!
I think they're gonna teach me how to be at one with the lifestream─attuned to its flow.
Maybe you're..."low on lifestream" or something?
Gonna need a bit more of that planet power!
Think we're gonna need to "top up."
I think you might need more spiritual energy.
How 'bout we take a quick breather?
Can't go lettin' our girl wear herself out!
Okay. But just for a bit.
I'm gettin' tired of this place.
Well, at least we have a way out.
Does it matter at this point?
Something gets in our way...we kill it.
I get the feelin' we're not welcome here.
Could try using that to bridge the gap.
Double time. Need to link up with the advance team.
Gotta be a way to get it down. Let's take a look.

Tower doesn't look too sturdy.
Think we could knock it over?
Hmph... I say we put this big asshole to work!
Like I said, still think we're better off having him do the heavy liftin'.
Alright! It's time to get pushin', people.
Dunno about you, but I'll take it.
Let's hang back─get ourselves some popcorn!
No time for that. Just take 'em out.
Man, I swear, you are no fun at all today.
Unless the monsters get you first.
Hey! Get a room, will ya?
Reno. You know what to do.
These assholes are better than I remember.
We kick ass and take names.

You ready to settle up?
'Cause I've been waitin' for this.
I'm so glad you're all okay!
Hmph! We're lucky you didn't crush us!
Yep! Can't keep Cloud and the others waiting.
I've got it this time. You'll see.
So it's their fault. Let's make 'em pay!
I think we're done here! Now, let's get back to it, shall we?
It's okay. We'll get to them.
Just need to find the path.
They should've been here by now. What's the holdup?
I'm sure we'll be fine! I have the utmost faith in you, sir!
It's been the honor of a lifetime to work with─
Look at 'em go! Bwok bwok bwok!
Sir. It's time we made a stand.
You saw the flags outside, didn't you?
The promised land belongs to Shinra now.
Sorry, Ancient. Ya snooze, ya lose!
Oh dear. Did you three get lost?
Three is still greater than two, you know.
And? So what if it is? Between me and Tseng, we got the strength of an army!
You're not getting past me... I'm a Turk, goddammit!
I'm so glad you're all okay!
Hmph! We're lucky you didn't crush us!

There's no time for this─like you said.
One of 'em's still ahead of us.
Built like a maze...remnants of battle...
It's not a temple─it's a fortress.
To defend against what, though? Fiends?
Humans feared and coveted the power of the Ancients. And so they slaughtered them.
It's not me you should be worried about!
I'm sorry...but I don't think it is.
Always did take my word for it.
I never hated you, you know.
This pedestal's a key. One only an Ancient can use.

"O warrior...weary though thou art...
inward must thou now turn.

"Reflect on thy long and bloody path...
and kindle life's fire anew.
"Forget not thine ire, for it shall...remake thee."
Rollin' out the red carpet for us?

Sorta.
We're each supposed to face some kind of trial.
I guess you...get to sit this one out.
I'll wait out here. But make it quick.
Well, no point delayin' the inevitable.
Don't forget my anger, huh? I'm gonna take that shit to the grave.
If the Cetra think I ain't pissed off enough, they are in for a rude awakening.
Hey, about Cloud... He's been acting kinda weird since we got here.
It's almost like he's... Actually, forget it.
We gotta go it alone from here.
Really wish we didn't have to, though.
Compared to the training we ninjas go through, this'll be a cakewalk.
Wanna bet a couple orbs of materia on who'll make it back first?
I don't have anything to prove.

Easy now... That is a valuable specimen;
it must be handled with the utmost care.
Come along, Number Thirteen. Don't be shy.

That's a good boy.
Make sure he's strapped down tight.

Such a fine red coat...
A rare specimen for my lucky thirteenth test.
Mako... Shinra... I'm sick of this.
I'm sick of all of this!
This is fine... Not scary at all.

Put the claws away, Boss.
Least while we're in Shinra territory.
Hey, Boss. Wanna try treading a little lighter this time? No point fighting if we don't have to.
Boss, I don't think we'll be back here anytime soon, so make sure you're ready for anything, okay?

If you won't come and claim him...
I can always keep him for myself.
Bet you're aching for a nice, hot shower.
This place is gonna thrive thanks to you!
Everything's gotten so much easier thanks to that reactor.

Alright, let's get you inside.
Someone's clearly had a long day.
Stopping at Sector 4 Undercity. Sector 4 Undercity.
What if... What if we went on an adventure?
Without the men in white? And the needles? Would you get better there?
I'm sorry, sweetie... I'm...spoiling our adventure...
Just wait here, alright? I'm gonna find a doctor.
Can't you find somewhere else to beg?
Good luck finding help around here.
Is there a doctor around here?

I'm sorry, honey, but I don't know.
I'm not from this part of town.

I have to go...
I don't wanna leave my mom alone too long.
Mommy has to...return to the planet.

Don't cry, sweetie. I'll always be with you.
Always and forever.

If you think about it, life and death
are just two sides of the same coin.

Our bodies may disappear when we die,
but our spirits still live on.

We return to the planet, rejoin the lifestream,
and─in time─give rise to new life.
I get it. I really do.
Knowing that the people we love aren't really gone? It doesn't make it any easier to let them go.
It still hurts. So we can't just think of it as a "homecoming." 'Cause it's not that simple.
We've all experienced pain. We all have our regrets.

What we've done─what's been done to us─
that's set in stone. The past is forever.

But the future─even if it has been written─
can be changed.

It's true that the pain and the anger
we carry can make us stronger.
But at what cost? What toll does it take?
I believe true strength doesn't come from any of that.

True strength comes from our ability to forgive─
to forge ahead in the hope of making things right.
So focus on the future─not the past.

Do that, and not even Sephiroth
will be able to stand in our way.
Tell me, though... Was it worth it?
All those lives cut short...at your hand.
Is what you're feeling even real?
It's time you stopped pretending, Cloud.
Your friend died in your arms.
And you didn't shed a tear.
Nothing but empty words to you.
For you are but a puppet─my puppet.
that you may burn your world to the ground─as I did.

You who walk in the footsteps
of we who dwell in eternity...

Listen well, for dusk is falling on
the age of our people─the Cetra.

And in the long night to come, others shall rise to claim stewardship of this planet─others who pay
no heed to history.
Though in time we triumphed over the calamity visited upon us by the stars, tragedy would nevertheless be our ultimate reward.
For the children of man feared us.
For the children of man envied us.
Perhaps their enmity was seeded by our celestial adversary.
Regardless, we had been forsaken by fate.
Abandoned to unquenchable anger and unbearable grief. Condemned and driven forth...
powerless to forestall the coming of our end.
Long ago, a wound marred the northern lands.

And to mend it did many venture forth,
only to meet with disaster.
A deceiver that stole the faces of the dead─of mothers and fathers, sisters and brothers lost.
With their voices did it sow the seeds of discord among our people─among the children of man.
For the planet did we lay down our lives in battle, and in death returned to her embrace.
Could not. Thus did it fall into a deep slumber.
And in the long silence of its sleep...
Heed well our warning of that which is to come:
When our adversary's scattered malignancy shall converge to plague the planet once more.
It has ever been our sacred duty to protect our planet against any who would threaten it.
They who came from without were one such threat.

The Gi, who with bitter prayer
forged the black materia.
So foul was the orb's magic that we knew at once it must be hidden, that none might ever wield its terrible power.

The black materia shall summon
the destroyer of worlds.

The meteor shall fall, sundering the skies
and shattering the earth.
I, son of Jenova, will at last claim my birthright.
My dominion shall reach into infinity.

It shall encompass worlds unbound by fate
and histories unwritten.

My fragmented mother, these errant worlds...
All shall be one again.
Your day of reckoning is here.
Yet you need not be afraid.
Still alive! No "homecomin'" for us today!
As if we were ever gonna lose. We're unstoppable!
Now where in the hell is he off to?

"Let those who seek our star's demise
find herein their rest."

If the black materia is removed,
the whole place comes down.
Please tell me that you're kidding!
We just have to return it to the altar.
It's too late! We can't stop it now.
Besides, there's no point fighting over a fake.
No... You're trying to fool me.
I'm back─just in the nick of time!

Run─while there's still time.
Leave the heavy liftin' to me!
No need to fret about a bot like me.
I wish I hadnae skipped leg day.

Cannae hold out for long, so run...
as if your lives depended on it!
I have secured us an exit.
Crap crap crappity crap crap crap!
I feel terrible about the way we treated Cait Sith.
Don't stop runnin'. Please don't stop.
Not sure...we're gettin' outta this one...
We can't let his death be in vain.
We won't. We're gonna make it!
Well then...y'all better pick up the pace!
Yeah, what he said! Shut up and run, dammit!
It was a good run...while it lasted...
You did...what you could... The rest...is up to them.
Now that's not a sight you see every day, eh?

If I popped my clogs,
they'd be sobbin' in the streets at the Saucer.
This beautiful body's but one of many!
So? Y'all get what you were after?
Didn't you hear what Aerith said?

which grants access to the true counterpart
hidden between worlds.
What in the world is going on?
Could it be? Has it finally begun!?
Yes, Cloud. Snap out of it.
I can't let you have this.
If she won't give it to us, we must take it.
Whatever happens, I'm here for you.
Behold... The true nature of reality.
When the boundaries of fate are breached, new worlds are born.

The planet encompasses a multitude
of worlds, ever unfolding.
Yet even the most resilient worlds are doomed to fade.
Nevertheless, their loss is not to be mourned.

For it is not death,
but a homecoming that awaits them.
And in the planet's embrace, all life is as one.

Should this world be unmade,
so too shall her children.

He'd tell you that he only cares about the planet.
That he'd do everything in his power to protect
and preserve it.
But this isn't the way it's supposed to be.
Oh, Cloud... I thought you might finally understand.
But what will you do with it? Let's see.
Let go of the past, Cloud.
We are to bear witness to the reunion of worlds.
I can feel him watching us.

But forget about him for now.
Just focus on yourself, okay?
Focus on you, Cloud─the one I've been trying to find. The real you.
Leave Sephiroth to me. I can handle him.

He's planning to use the black materia,
but I won't let that happen.
He has to be stopped─by a Cetra.
Thanks for returning it to me, Cloud. I appreciate it.
But now, it belongs with you.
Didn't know if it was mako poisoning or the degradation, but I thought you were done for.

Well, you can thank me for the ride later.
Gotta find Aerith first.

She told us that an ancient city lies just beyond
these woods─and that the Cetra built a very special
altar there.
That's where she's headed; I'm sure of it.
Problem is, Sephiroth stole the black materia...

meaning he could destroy
the entire planet any minute!
And Aerith said she's the only one who can stop him!
We got separated in the fog and...
And how can you be so sure?
So, Cloud... I heard something from Aerith.
She said Sephiroth kicked the ever-livin' crap outta you back in the Temple of the Ancients.
You heard wrong. Didn't go down like that.
Okay... Then how exactly did he get the materia from you?
You don't always have to play the badass, y'know.
Alright, fine, you win. He beat the shit outta me and took the materia.

It's kinda mine too. I shoulda been there for you,
but I wasn't.
Musta been some dream you were havin'.
Judgin' by the way your eyes were twitchin'.
Don't know if I'd call it a dream...
Either way, somethin' happened to you, didn't it?
Yeah. Got sent to another world.
Apparently, there's at least a few more than one.
I'd explain, but don't think I can.
S'alright... Doubt I'd wanna hear it anyway.
Is it just me, or...is there something weird about this mist?
Do you see them in it too? The Whispers?
I'm afraid to say it, but...
if the Whispers control fate, then...does that mean we were destined to be separated from Aerith?
Why'd I have to open my mouth?
If you start feeling sick or...thinking weird thoughts...you'll let us know. Okay?
For example...stuff like...thinking...I'm not the real me.
You don't have to apologize─but I do want you to talk. To me─or someone at least.
I've apologized to everyone else, but not to you. So...

I'm sorry for givin' the keystone to Shinra.
I truly am.
I just thought that, since it was so dangerous, I'd rather something happened to one of them than to one of you.

You're a good man, Cloud.
I don't deserve your forgiveness.
Oh, I'm still pretty pissed. Just got bigger fish to fry.
Right...that makes sense. Still, I'll do what I can to help, and we'll fry those fish together!

The grand metropolis,
where the Ancients once gathered to pray...
You know, I think it is!
Yeah─Gramps told me all about it when I was growing up. He called it "the forgotten capital."

Said it was the heart of Cetran civilization...
but I never thought I'd see it!

And this place screams fancy altar!
Aerith's gotta be here!
Well then, let's go get our girl.
I'm gonna go out on a limb and say those assholes are fixin' to get in our way again.

Yeah...they're different.
Don't belong to fate or the planet.

when spite and sorrow are harvested
to feed the planet!
Dunno, but they sure don't like us.
Time to wreak some serious havoc!
Not goin' down without a fight!
This is what you get for crossing a ninja!
I'll be damned. It's like we're back on the expressway.
How're we supposed to get through?
Just gotta say the magic words:
I know I'm doing this wrong. Mom never taught me how to pray.
And as the last living Cetra, I may never learn.
So, please...tell me how to do that.

It engulfs fleeting moments of joy,
transforming them into rage, sadness, hatred.
Never have I felt them so keenly.

However...you'll never see the truth
with such clouded eyes.
White as far as the eye can see...
Well, nice to see you too.
I hear you've been pretty busy.
Uh, how's about we save the catching up for later?
Just as worlds unite, so too do they part.
You think they took him somewhere?
What in the hell is going on!?

And, whatever happens...
protect your honor as a SOLDIER!
And, whatever happens...protect your honor as a SOLDIER!
You gotta be kiddin' me! He still ain't dead!?
Because he knows this isn't over.
Can't stay here forever. We'd best get movin'.
Anyway...you haven't seen Viceroy Sarruf, have you?

He failed to show at an important event─
made us look like fools.

Maybe he wouldn't have if you'd
spent some money on that set.

Ah, you're probably right.
Rich kids do like things just so.

Still got results, though, even without him.
Resistance elements are more fired up than ever.

I'm onto you. This war's nothing but
a ploy to distract me from Sephiroth.
Regardless, the plan is already in motion.
Regardless, the plan is already in motion.
A father's dream...accomplished by his son.
A father's dream...accomplished by his son.
I want the real thing, not some imitation.
But an imitation's all you deserve.
In the back─just like old times.
Nah, I couldn't have dreamt that.
It all felt way too real.
"Just as worlds unite, so too do they part."
But who's to say they can't unite again?
Can you not raise it just a wee bit higher?
So, what'd Aerith actually do anyway?
And with that, we are cleared for takeoff!
You have to promise not to look up.
Fine, but don't let it get to you.
Don't let what get to me?
It's not real. Just an illusion.
Now let's go get Sephiroth. He's hiding up north.
Trust me, he is. SOLDIER's intuition.
Oh yeah? Better hope you're right.

Just remember─we got everything ridin' on this.
And that's a load you'd best be ready to carry.
No heavy loads! We're close to capacity as it is!
Don't worry about me. I can handle it.
You gonna be okay getting back?
And if I said I wasn't?
Don't worry. It's like a second home.
Thanks. I'll keep an eye out.

I'll put everything I've got into my prayers.
I'll stop the meteor.
And...I'll leave the rest to you. Good luck.
You willnae get away with this!
You've done it before─can do it again.

Better than that thing's
gonna be in a few minutes!
I got it right where I want it!
Yeah! Let's get this show on the road!
Haha! Couldn'ta said it better myself!

You gotta admit─it's been awesome
having me on the team, right?

You can say that again.
It's been a real trip.
Y'all ready to close it out in style!?
Long as you guys can keep up!
Lady Luck's brought us this far!
And the rest is up to us!
Can ya help with that, Cloud?
Look at you takin' charge! I like it!

What the hell happened to you? You were
a SOLDIER! How could you turn your back
on everything we stand for!?

Long as you get what you want,
who cares who gets hurt! Is that it!?

Rage, my weak little puppet...
It's almost endearing.

Don't care how big you get...
I'm not backing down.
I'm finishing this!
This is bad! This is very bad!
We don't have time for this!
Alright, scaly! Move it or lose it!
C'mon, we gotta take out Bahamut!

That's some bullshit─
bringin' it back like that.
Lemme take care of those wings for ya!

Anyone else think we should
clip the big lad's wings!?
Heh heh... Aw, did that hurt?
Time to take out the other!
Let's settle this once and for all!
Hey, butthead here's lookin' pretty banged up!

Call me crazy, but it feels like
someone's helping us!
Let's pay 'em back in kind, alright!?
We've gotta take out the barrier!
These gross feathers have gotta go!
We've gotta take out the barrier!
We're on the home straight now!
Let's show him what we're made of!

I saw what you did back there, Cloud.
Thank you.
Thank me later. This ain't over.

What do you make of this, Cloud? Is any
of it real? Or is it all just a fever dream?

Don't even bother. That shit won't
work on me─not anymore.
How can you want this, Sephiroth?
How can you want an eternity of loneliness?

Eyes afire with purpose...though yet a stripling.
One whose mettle must be tested.

An untethered soul
Adrift in the void of time
This bridge his makefast
The singular item that you now hold...

is possessed of a power beyond your ken!
You will deliver it unto me!
Very well. Then I shall take it from you by force!

You are indeed a worthy warrior. I saw it plain,
and never does my judgment err.
Lemme guess: the sand giant. That was you?
Drawn were you by Genji's call, and whither did it lead you but those sweltering sands.
Let us share a drink beneath the stars.
Hmph. I offer to reward your fruitless labors, yet you refuse to accept.
You've absconded with nigh every Genji piece I own. Is there a name more befitting than "thief"!?
To wit, you've made off with six:
my helm and breastplate; my gloves and greaves. However!
One item eludes your avaricious grasp.
You fool! 'Tis the aegis of Genji!
Once the full set is again in my possession, my memories shall at last return...
and I will know not only whence I came, but whither I must go!
And thus! In the name of Genji, I issue one final challenge!
Face me, the true bladesman of legend─Gilgamesh!
We shall duel on the isle I call home:
I eagerly await the day our blades cross─the day I reclaim what is mine!
Silence! You caught me unawares once, but it will not happen again!

Burning desire
To reclaim my stolen prize
Rages evermore

Confound it...
Without the power of Genji, I am outmatched.
The mere sight of it has kindled in me a covetous desire!
Could it be─that a hunger for weapons brought me hither?
Wherefore does the memory elude me!?
Return what you have stolen─my Genji!
Not until you return...what is mine...
Only then shall you know peace─but not until that day!
At long last, the knave returns!

Beneath the moonlight
In vict'ry shall I revel
My Genji─
None other. After analyzing the phenomena associated with your sudden disappearance...
I was able to devise a way in which to join you virtually.
No matter! Begone, foul conjurer, or I shall make this place your grave!
You must tell me about yourself─and about this place!
Such impudence! A wanton display of disrespect!
Ah! Whoa! What did I say!?
Apologies, but I am presently detained in...the privy!
This is it...the mysterious landmass I've wanted to see since it first appeared. Gilgamesh Island!
It's pristine despite having been submerged...
I assume the ocean must have shielded it from the magnetic fields.
But the question remains. How does a once-submerged island catalyze a dimensional distortion?
It certainly gets the gears turning!
To review, we're after the Genji equipment─formerly known as protorelics...
as well as the bladesman of legend who covets them.
Both should be somewhere on this island─but where?
And that is the last thing I would like you to investigate!
Oh, how I have longed for this moment!
Ever since they left my care, I have been counting the minutes until their return!
Yes, you rogues. 'Tis I! The Genji's chosen keeper─and I demand you relinquish them forthwith!

My shining beacons of martial prowess!
Blemished and begrimed and befouled!
How could you be so utterly remiss in their care!?
